Dialogs.Dialog: Manaka
Hey, a question.
Huh？
I've been wondering about this since grade school. Why are guys always so energetic during the cleaning period？
Hmm, I also wonder why.
They pretend to get into sword battles, and they play baseball or something else.
If they put that energy into cleaning, they could finish it much faster.
Haha, that's right.
How can I make them focus on cleaning？ Do you have any ideas？
Rather, why don't you try to join in and have fun with them？ Try and find out the truth, Great Detective Manaka！
...Don't answer half- heartedly. Just forget it.
(I really thought it was a nice idea, though...)
By the way, how has the cleaning case gone？
Manaka
I warned the guys a little bit and what they said was... "Takane is always serious."
That's your good point. But I don't think they still think of you that way, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.
It's fine. It's true anyway...
But...
I don't think it's good to have people say that to me too often.
Now, I'm considering the method you suggested earlier.
My method... Was it...？
Hehe... I'm not going to let them off easily.
(Now she's burning with an unyielding spirit...！)
How did it go？ I mean, with the cleaning event, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.
Manaka
Haha, I beat them on everything, from sword fighting to baseball.
A-As expected... And then？
Um, and then... Well...
Hmm？
Playing with the guys was really fun.
So, I made a condition that we could play once we finished cleaning, and they finished the cleaning really fast.
...Now, occasionally, I become their comrade.
Eh！？
Ah, only occasionally. Just when they don't have enough people... So, you don't have to worry.
(It's something she couldn't do in her childhood, so she is enjoying it now, huh？)
Did you enjoy sword fighting during the cleaning period？
Manaka
Haha, the guys did.
Eh？ How about you then, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
I was concentrating on the cleaning, since I already accomplished what I wanted to do.
I see. I kind of wanted to see you dueling with a sword though, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.
...There's also another reason I quit.
I played so seriously that people started gathering to watch... I even got scouted by someone from the fencing club.
The fencing club？
Yeah. I was told, "You have potential. It's not too late to start now！".
It's impossible, and for a girl to join the fencing club, it's just... Well...
Anyway, it was fun. Thanks to you, now I have experienced something new in this world. Thank you.
(I feel like I helped her open the door to a new world somehow...)
Manaka
Here. These are some sweets I made during home economics class. They are black soy bean cookies.
Oh, thank you. I'll eat them at home.
Hehe, you really have to eat them. I went through hardships for them.
Went through hardships, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Making them wasn't that difficult, but...
A girl in my group tasted one of them and said it was delicious, and then other girls from different groups came to try them.
I thought I had made plenty of them, but when I realized it, only five were left. That was such a surprise.
Things went out of control, huh...？
Yeah, it was like that. Now, I'm getting scared of the next cooking class.
Next time we have to make a madeleine cake and the amount I can bake is limited...
(Seems like it's gonna cause an uproar...)
How was your home economics class？
Manaka
Oh, yeah, here is your portion of the madeleine cake.
Thank you... You wrapped it very nicely.
Yes. I had to protect this last piece with my life. It was quite an uproar. How should I put it...？
It was like a scene you saw in news reports about bargain sales on New Year's.
Wow... To that extent...
If you have to cook something next time, you don't have to bring it back for me. I'll be fine.
Thank you. Hehe. Now, all my tiredness has gone away.
The next class is handicraft, so I should be fine... Probably.
(You said "Probably"？ Even you weren't sure about it ▲高嶺＊＊▲？)
Was everything okay during home economics class？
Manaka
The class was fine, but things went crazy when we learned that we were making desserts next.
It became a big uproar, and I ended up promising to let everyone try my desserts.
I see... But how come things turned out like that？
I wonder why. This never happened before. It only happened after I started dating you...
Wait a minute！ I didn't do anything！！？
...Right. Sorry. But I can't think of other reasons.
Why is that...？
(You changed since we started dating, huh, ▲高嶺＊＊▲...？)
About the home economics class, did you find out the reason, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Manaka
Not yet, Watson. The mystery has deepened.
Hahaha, let me give you a hint.
You often say that you have changed since we met right, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Yeah.
What if we aren't the only ones who noticed？
...You mean, the reason everyone has changed is because I've changed...？
I wonder. How about you ask them next time？
...Okay！ I will！
(Can I say that this case is closed this time？)
Manaka
By the way, there were a lot of students sleeping during physics class.
Haha, the sensei's voice sounded like a lullaby to them, I guess.
They were sleeping soundly, even tossing left and right.
And one of the guys pushed a pencil box off the desk while he was asleep.
Ah, yeah. Something like that could happen.
Hehe. And that guy was startled by the sound and suddenly stood up. You know what he said？
He shouted, "I'm not sleeping！" out loud, but the sensei didn't get angry at him.
Why？
He seemed to be amused by what that student said.
The sensei couldn't stop laughing until the class ended. I wonder if he'll be able to concentrate on teaching next time.
I can't wait until the next class, but I'm also worried that my class will fall behind schedule. Anyway, I can't wait.
(You're looking forward to it, huh？)
How was your physics class？
Manaka
The sensei really tried his best.
Which means he didn't laugh in the classroom？
Yeah, but...
Although physics class was usually boring, he changed the pace somehow, so not as many students fell asleep this time.
Hmm... It was an unexpected improvement then.
I guess. But even so, that guy was still falling asleep.
Hahaha, did he do anything funny again this time？
Yeah, a lot of people were looking forward to it. I'd prefer that he paid more attention in class.
...But I was also hoping for something fun. Just a little.
(You're really looking forward to it, huh...？)
How's that guy doing？
Manaka
Ah, the one that usually falls asleep in class？
Usually, his head would tilt left and right when he dozed off, but this time it was swaying back and forth.
His head almost hit the chair when it tilted back, and when it finally returned forward, it hit the desk like "Bang"！
That must gave hurt...
Yeah, I think it hurt. His pencil box was dented and his forehead was all red.
Whoa...
But this should teach him to pay attention in class, right？
The class has become more enjoyable, so he should take it seriously. It's killing two birds with one stone.
...But it'll be a little disappointing not being able to see any more funny things in class.
(I wonder if he'll stop falling asleep in class.)
How's that guy who usually falls asleep in class？
Manaka
Things didn't go perfectly but he didn't fall asleep as much as he used to.
It must hurt badly when he hit his head on the desk.
I guess so, but now he seems to really enjoy physics.
Why is that？
He finds it interesting now that he had a first-hand experience of pendulum mechanisms when he dozed off last time.
I doubt if such mechanisms are related to physics...
I doubt it too. Anyway, it was kind of his self- awakening.
Yeah, certainly.
Seeing that student, the sensei also got fired up. I think physics class has become totally different now.
(I kind of look forward to my physics class, too.)
Manaka
My next P.E. class will be creative dance.
Huh？ Creative dance？
Yeah, we have to form a team and think about a choreography to match the music, but...
But？
There's one girl in my group that's very good at dancing, so everyone is letting her design the dance moves.
Isn't that good？ Seems like your group has the advantage.
Yeah, but I wonder if it'll turn out to be outrageous. I'm a little worried.
Outrageous？
All my teammates are from sports clubs. They'll certainly decide on some difficult moves.
I'm getting very nervous. What should I do if I can't dance？ I hope everything goes well...
(It's unusual to see you lacking confidence ▲高嶺＊＊▲.)
How's your dancing team doing？
Manaka
Eh？ Ah, you know...
We had decided on the choreography. Our dance moves are better than other groups.
Uh-huh, I see.
All the members have memorized the moves by now, but...
...But？
...Hey, do you think I have bad sense of rhythm？
Eh？ But you've played the piano since you were a kid, and you learned ballet too, ▲高嶺＊＊▲...
Yeah, I know. That's also what I thought...
There must be something wrong... Hmm...
(Did she stumble during the dance？ But that's kind of surprising.)
How did your dance practice go, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Manaka
Well, I'm not doing too well... Everyone also said that just a little bit more and I could catch up.
Okay.
But, my team's turn is during this coming week... I...
...▲高嶺＊＊▲. Are you free after this？
Huh？ I'm thinking about going home to practice the dance moves.
How about taking a break today？ It's not good to worry about it too much... And I also want to be of some help.
You... You will teach me how to dance？
Yeah. If you can make a joke like that, then you're fine. Let's go have some tea.
I want to eat cake.
Fine. I'll treat you this time.
Hehe. Yay！ ...Thanks. Now I feel better.
(At least, this is what I can do to help you... I'm rooting for you, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.)
Manaka
Hey, want to hear the latest？
What？
I got full score for the creative dance！
Oh, you did it！
Yeah, thanks to you. After I spent some time with you, I felt refreshed. And the next day, my body simply followed the rhythms.
It reminded me of the first time I rode a bicycle without training wheels.
Ah, I kind of understand that feeling.
Hehe... Hey, if you ever feel stressed from anything, tell me, okay？
If it's something you can't say, just lean on me. I'll always be by your side.
...I'm kidding！ Hey, this time, let me treat you. What do you want to eat？
(Yay！)
Manaka
Say, have you heard about a fortune teller in our school whose predictions are very accurate？
A fortune teller？
Yeah. Seems like you won't be able to find out who this person is unless you are recommended by old customers.
Very high security, huh？
Yeah.
Are you interested in fortune telling？
Yeah, usually I read my fortunes from a magazine, but I've never seen a fortune teller in person.
Aren't you curious about your fortune？
Hmm, I don't know...
Geez. Whatever. I'll ask others about this then.
(I wonder what do you want to ask the fortune teller, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.)
Have you learned anything more about the fortune teller？
Manaka
No, none of my classmates has ever met that fortune teller.
But we've been talking about it.
I see. By the way, what do you want to ask her, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Huh？
Maybe I should stop.
Huh？ Why？
Everything is good now. What if I were told that the future would be bad...？
Hmm, in that case... Hmm...
(She seems to be rather hesitant...)
You gave up looking for the fortune teller, right ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Manaka
...Yeah.
Why was that？
I gave up. Although I already gave up...
I finally got some leads about that fortune teller.
Haha... Maybe you can call it fate, huh？
...No, it's not.
Huh...？
...Um, actually, I kind of wanted to...
Haha, if you really want to, just go for it.
Um... Maybe. Hmm...
(Why do you hesitate so much like this？)
Hey, have you met that fortune teller yet？
Manaka
No, I think I will leave it rest.
I was just curious about my future, but if it's about my own future, I should be the one to control it.
Haha, that sounds more like you, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.
Hehe, I'm just determined. I'm kidding.
By the way, who's this fortune teller？
It's the one at the consultation room...
...It's a secret.
Eh？ Tell me.
No, this is a secret among girls.
Okay, okay.
Manaka
Do you know where the most famous spot in our school is？
Hmm... The rooftop？
The rooftop ranks third.
Then... where？
The most famous one is the courtyard.
Who told you？
The newspaper club did a survey. They were searching for the best spot for a nap.
But they didn't share much info about the exact spot because it would be bad if that spot became too famous.
Now I feel like I want to look for that spot, too.
Really？ How about we both secretly search for it？
Yeah, let's do that, Holmes.
Okay, Watson. Hehe！
We really can't find the best spot for napping, huh？
Manaka
Yeah, now no one can take a nap.
Maybe since so many people are searching around there, it's hard to find a place to take a nap.
Well, I think that's a possible reason.
Say, did you remember hearing people shout "If Peter Piper picked a peck of pickled peppers" on the way here？ What was that？
Wasn't that the drama club？ It was just their vocal exercises, I think.
I see. So that place wouldn't be fit for a napping spot then.
Hmm... I feel like we might have overlooked something important...
If Holmes can't solve this case, then...
Watson, you have to help me. Geez.
...Okay, I'm sorry.
Manaka
Hey, I have an idea...
Oh！ Go on, Holmes.
Hehe. Just be quiet and listen, Watson.
The news article might be a lie. There could be better places for a nap. The courtyard was just a decoy.
Really？ You really did some research, eh？
Yeah, I heard about this from someone in the drama club.
Ah, since they were doing their exercises nearby. You really are brilliant, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.
...Sorry, but you got me wrong.
I went to ask them what followed "If Peter Piper picked a peck of pickled peppers" and napping spots randomly came up.
Holmes...
Hmm... The following part is "Where's the peck of pickled peppers Peter Piper picked？" It's a nursery rhyme, you know？
(Hmm...？ Should I be impressed by this？)
Manaka
We really can't find the napping spot.
Yeah, if the newspaper club didn't publish that article, it wouldn't have caused this much uproar.
Hehe. It has become the talk of the town, huh？ ...But it's too bad.
I want to be there with you.
Really？
Yeah, if we could find a quiet spot at school, we could relax there. But there's no such spot.
It would be nice if we could lie down on the ground whenever we wanted.
Yeah, that would be nice...
But it was fun, so it's not too bad. I now understand Holmes' feelings a bit better. Nice job, Watson. I'll be counting on you.
Yeah, sure thing, Holmes.
...Teeheehee！
Hahaha...
Manaka
Have you noticed that the clock in our gym is really behind？
Ah, I heard that no one gives it a tune-up. That's why it's behind.
Well, it's not that no one adjusts it...
What do you mean？
Someone fixed it, but it slowed down again.
T-That's...
It's troublesome that they can't find the reason, right？ This must be bad for people in sports clubs.
But why can't it be fixed？ ...This is mysterious.
(Will this become part of our school's seven wonders or that sort of thing？)
I heard that they were trying to repair the clock at the gym.
Manaka
Ah, right. Now, I feel relieved.
But what if it's beyond repair？
In that case, they can buy a new one, right？
...Hmm.
What？
Can't you act a little more scared when I talk about something scary...？
Ah~~！ It's scary~~！
...S-Something like that？
...I think that's enough.
(That "Ah~~！" she just made was priceless！)
Manaka
Say, have you heard about that clock？
Yeah. They were trying to repair it again.
But didn't they say that it was beyond repair？
In that case, it could become "that thing", right？
Then it could become a haunted clock, or something like that... I guess I've heard about that...
...As I thought. You're not scared at all.
Ah！！ I told you I would not do that anymore.
But...
...If you show me how to do that first, I'll follow you.
Me！？ Okay... A-Ah~~！ It's scary~~！ How's that！？
...I won't do it after all.
What！？
Manaka
They finally removed that clock.
It ended just like that...
They will install a new clock. This time we will see if something happens.
If it delays again, this will become a real scary story.
I hope it delays.
...Just kidding.
...Geez.
Have you heard that there is some treasure buried somewhere in our school, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Manaka
Buried treasure？ Haha, did someone try to spread a joke？
That was what I thought, but it has become a widespread rumor recently.
I wonder who started the rumor.
The person who did this might have an ulterior motive behind it.
Like, using treasure hunting to make people become greedy. Someone might gain something from this, don't you think？
Haha, don't tell me...
I'm looking forward to your follow-up report.
(No way. Is she really taking it seriously？)
Manaka
Did you find more info about the buried treasure？
Yeah, now more people are starting to talk about trying to dig for it.
Even the teaching staff got interested in this, too.
Ahem...
Oh！ It's the Great Detective Takane's turn.
Hehe. Have you considered anyone who might want the ground in the school dug？
Could it be...
In this case, people will be tricked into digging the school grounds for free.
Will they find ghosts, or snakes...？ Hehe, I can't wait to see how it turns out.
(She's so into her mystery novel character...)
Wanna hear about the buried treasure？
Manaka
Any progress？
At last, even the alumni heard about it and started coming to school. The rumor has really spread far.
I see...
Huh？
If it's something even the alumni would pay attention to, it might be something like...
Like what？
A time capsule. Finding the one you buried must be quite a tough job.
Ah, you're right！
But if that's not the case, I doubt who spread the rumor about buried treasure...
If we could only find the rumor's source...
Have you heard that the mystery about the buried treasure had been solved？
Manaka
Really？ What happened in the end？
The rumor started from a treasure map that a grade-schooler drew.
A grade-schooler？
Yeah, he's the brother of a student here. That kid showed his drawing to his older brother and his brother made up the joke.
People would have noticed immediately that it was a fake treasure map...
But the paper he used was some old paper from the Edo period, so it looked real.
Haha, so that's how it was.
Well, although it ended up like that, some alumni really did find the time capsules they buried.
Hehe, I could say that it was just as what I predicted.
Yeah, you were right.
Hehe, if there's something like this again, let's try to solve it. It's fun▼
Manaka
There's a new transfer student in my class...
Eh？ Could it be a girl？
...You shouldn't be concerned about that.
I was joking. And？
Geez... And although she's a nice girl, she really loves competitions.
According to her, I am her rival.
...What does that mean？
In the classroom, if I raised my hand, she also raised hers. During P.E. class, she declared that she wouldn't lose to me.
Hmm... That's interesting.
Yeah, it's fun. I'll have to think how I should deal with her. Now, I feel like the atmosphere in my class has become more cheerful.
(Hmm, it seems to be fun.)
How's everything going with your rival？
Manaka
Hehe. There was a contest to find who could buy a tonkatsu sandwich, and she tried to compete with other guys in my class.
Hahaha, and what was the result？
She was really upset because she couldn't buy any. That tonkatsu sandwich sure is popular.
I heard. I also want to try one.
You want to, huh？ ...Ah.
What？
Next time, I'll join the contest. If I can get one, I'll share it with you.
You will join the contest ▲高嶺＊＊▲！？
Yeah, I don't think it's good to run in the halls, but if it's just once, it should be fine.
I have no choice. It will be my first time running down the hallway. Now, I'm quite nervous...
(You will be running down the hallway... The whole school will be surprised ▲高嶺＊＊▲.)
By the way, how was the tonkatsu sandwich？ Did your rival get to buy one？
Manaka
In the end, the contest was canceled.
So she gave up already？
No, but this time, she's trying to find out the shopkeeper's weakness instead.
...So, it turned out that way, huh？
Hehe, she's so persistent, right？ I'll have to learn from her, too.
I think you are already a very persistent person, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.
Really？ But I don't think I'm as persistent as her.
Ah, I wonder if I can also find a way to get that tonkatsu sandwich.
(Hmm, that girl influenced you a great deal ▲高嶺＊＊▲...)
Did you find the shopkeeper's weakness？
Manaka
Hehe, of course not. So, we decided to try to make the sandwich by ourselves instead.
Haha, it sure is easier that way. So, this is the outcome of the contest, huh？
Not the outcome. Now, it turned out to be a competition.
A competition？
Yeah, we'll see who makes a tonkatsu sandwich that tastes closest to the original.
That sounds unreasonable...
Hehe, but I don't think I'll lose to her.
Is that so？ How have you two done in the competitions so far？
Of course, I won all of them. I won, and I'll always win. I'm kidding.
(If they continue to do this, will they become eternal rivals？)
Manaka
You know Mori-sensei, the history sensei, right？
Ah, that old sensei.
Hehe, so you know him. He's going to retire soon.
Really...？
It's sad.
Do you enjoy Mori-sensei's class？
Yes, very much. The way he talks is so gentle and he knows his subject so well.
The way he talks is so gentle that a lot of students fall asleep.
Hehe, his tone of voice must make them feel at peace.
It's sad that he will leave us soon...
Yeah...
Mori-sensei's retirement is approaching...
Manaka
Yeah... I've been thinking what I can do to repay him for his kindness, but I still have no idea.
To repay his kindness...？ For you, what you can do best is to pay full attention in his class, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.
Hmm？ You say it like you don't pay attention in his class.
No, no. I didn't mean that.
Hehe, geez. But that might be the only thing I can do.
I should convince everyone in my class to do so.
Ah, that might be good.
Okay, I'll try. Thanks for your nice idea.
(I hope it turns out well.)
Everything's been going great during Mori-sensei's class, huh？
Manaka
Yeah, everyone paid full attention in his class.
And not many students fell asleep.
Hehe, right. Even Mori- sensei was surprised...
He was, and he seemed happy.
No, it's nothing. I was thinking that he's going to leave us soon, and I suddenly felt sad...
There are still a lot of things I want to discuss with him...
Finally, Mori-sensei has left.
Manaka
Yeah. I gave him a letter...
A letter？
Yeah, to thank him for all his hard work and to wish him happiness... It sounds funny, but I couldn't do anything else.
I see. He must've been happy to receive that.
Yeah, he seemed happy...
He said "Takane-san is a student that I'm proud to have taught" and that made me happy...
Don't make that face. I just feel a little bit lonely. This isn't something to feel sad about...
If there's a chance, we should meet him again...
Manaka
Ah！
What's wrong？
What is that boy over there carrying？
Ah, that's a handheld game console.
I see... Is it okay to bring something like that to school？
It will be confiscated if the sensei sees it. Do you mean you've see other people carrying them？
Yes, many of the girls in my class have them.
They said that the games are very "moe." I wonder what kind of games they're playing.
Yeah... I wonder what kind of "moe" they meant...
What kind？
(How can I explain to her what "moe" is...？)
Manaka
Hey, we talked about the game consoles that many girls here have, right？
Yeah, we did.
Say, when they said "moe," they meant "cute.", right？
Oh, so that's what they meant.
But, "moe" means something more than just cute.
When I told them I didn't understand, they offered to lend me the game. I refused though, since I don't own the console.
Hey, are there other ways to experience this "moe" besides playing games？
I can't think of other ways right now.
Hmm, somehow I really want to know. I want to find out what "moe" really is.
(For you, I don't think you would understand it even if I tried to explain, ▲高嶺＊＊▲...)
Manaka
I think I'm starting to understand what "moe" is.
Did something happen？
I just tried playing that game for a little bit.
For a little bit？
My friend said that I almost got all the characters, which means I had completed nearly all the routes.
I see. Hmm, I sense some danger coming.
Danger？
Come on you get absorbed into things very easily, don't you, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Are games like this highly addictive？
It depends, I think. Anyway, don't get so addicted to games that you forget about me, okay？
As if that will ever happen. Hehe.
(...I hope this isn't the Bad End flag for my love life...)
Hey, are you still playing games？
Manaka
Well, the game console was broken.
That girl said that she pushed it so hard that the buttons stopped working.
Such an intense player.
So, I'll have to wait for another chance to learn more about "moe."
Huh？ What's wrong？
I'm just thinking that the flag has been removed.
The flag？
Ah, no, it's nothing. That's disappointing, huh？
No, it's okay. Hey, let's think about where we should go to for our next date.
Manaka
Hey, has the new music sensei taught your class yet？
No, not yet. Did something happen？
Yeah, the music class has become much more fun. We had to do some warm-ups before the chorus class.
Warm-ups？
Yeah, light exercises and stretching.
What would exercising do with music？
When you sing, you have to use various muscles in your body, so it's good to warm up those muscles first.
Really？
The most enjoyable part was the self-introduction. You can look forward to your first class with this sensei.
I still feel like laughing just thinking about it... Hahaha！
(Hmm, now I'm getting curious...)
Manaka
How was your music class？
"If you don't eat well, you can't sing！ Eat 'em up！" That's what he said！
Yeah！ He really doesn't seem like a music sensei, does he？
He's more like a P.E. sensei.
But he was the first sensei to tell me that music is about enjoying the notes. He really made me feel at ease.
He made you feel at ease？
Yeah, because I don't like to lose, I always put all my effort into things I'm doing.
Maybe I can just have fun during the music class. I can't wait for the next class！
How's the music class going？
Manaka
Well, I was asked to play the piano. But I can't look at the music sheet.
Will you be okay then？
Yeah, I've heard the tune so many times that I've learned how to play it. This is like a challenge from the sensei.
Hahaha, he really did it.
Hehe... Hey, thanks for always listening to me.
Why did you say that all of a sudden？
Well, the first person to tell me not to be too serious was you.
If it weren't for you, I wouldn't be able to enjoy music class like I do now. That's why I thanked you.
Okay, you're welcome. Good luck for your recital.
Yeah！
How was your recital？
Manaka
Well, I could play the song, but...
But？
I was told that I didn't enjoy it enough.
What？
"You should improvise a little more." he said. Argh... That Kawai-sensei really confuses me.
He can outwit you, huh？
Yeah. Next time, I'll play more freely then.
Yeah, just do it.
Hehehe！ You must root for me.
